						               													<description>In this expansion, the Pass action is replaced with the Play an Action Card option.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There are several Action Cards available:&amp;#10;- Discard a bull card &amp;#10;- Discard a china card from the general display &amp;#10;- Draw a money card &amp;#10;- Exchange a china card you own with a china card from the general display &amp;#10;- Replace all bull cards with new ones &amp;#10;- Make the player to your right play&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Play with the basic rules with the following additions.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Additional material:&amp;#10;14 action cards (6 sorts)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Preparation:&amp;#10;The pass cards are not needed, remove them from the game.&amp;#10;Shuffle the new action cards. &amp;#10;Each player gets two and keeps them secret from the others.&amp;#10;Make a draw pile from the rest.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Game play:&amp;#10;On each player&amp;rsquo;s turn, they may either:&amp;#10;Buy a china card &amp;#10;or&amp;#10;Take a bull card &amp;#10;or&amp;#10;Play an action card&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Play an action card:&amp;#10;The player plays an action card (=&amp;gt; discard pile) and fulfills the action, if he likes. &amp;#10;Then the next player has his turn.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Action card pile exhausted:&amp;#10;Shuffle the discard pile and build a new draw pile.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Loose more than one china card:&amp;#10;The player gets the money card as usual and an additional action card from the draw pile, if available.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
